<paragraph blockId="5.[178,1085,1426,1594]" pageId="5" pageNumber="982">
This species group currently includes three species (see below) distributed in the southern East Palaearctic and 
<collectingRegion box="[427,510,1455,1477]" country="Morocco" name="Oriental" pageId="5" pageNumber="982">Oriental</collectingRegion>
regions. It is distinguished from other species groups by dilated protarsomeres I-IV, from other species groups represented in the East Palaearctic and 
<collectingRegion box="[222,305,1513,1535]" country="Morocco" name="Oriental" pageId="5" pageNumber="982">Oriental</collectingRegion>
regions also by larger body size, denser punctation of the forebody, a male sternite VIII with a shallow or small posterior excision, and a slender, weakly sclerotized, and practically symmetric aedeagus with a small hooked apex.
</paragraph>
